content:
Yes, there have been many modern pop songs that have featured the saxophone:

- "Talk" by Khalid
- "I Don’t Care" by Ed Sheeran and Justin Bieber
- "Dancing With A Stranger" by Sam Smith and Normani
- "Youngblood" by 5 Seconds of Summer
- "Want You Back" by 5 Seconds of Summer
- "Shallow" by Lady Gaga and Bradley Cooper
- "Thunder" by Imagine Dragons
- "Wolves" by Selena Gomez and Marshmello

These are just a few examples of modern pop songs that feature the saxophone. The saxophone continues to be a popular instrument in pop music, and it's exciting to see how it's being incorporated in new and innovative ways.
